 Friday, July 30, 2004  Fine Print				 				 				 																Sound of Simon																																	 New York, July 29 (Reuters): Folk-rock troubadours Paul Simon and Art Garfunkel will end their Old Friends reunion tour with a free concert in front of Romes historic Colosseum on Saturday, the duos publicist said yesterday.																																	The concert, which will also include the harmony singing Everly Brothers, will mark Simon amp; Garfunkels first appearance together in Italy.																																	 and Garfunkel, both 62, with more than 40 million records sold in the US including such hits as The Sound of Silence and Bridge Over Troubled Waters, kicked off the tour in October. It is their first concert tour as a duo in some 20 years.
